class ListNode {
    constructor(val, next = null) {
        this.val = val;
        this.next = next;
    }
}

function sortedList(head) {
    if (!head || !head.next) return head;

    let prev = head;
    let cur = head.next;

    while (cur) {
        if (cur.val < prev.val) {
            prev.next = cur.next;
            cur.next = head;
            head = cur;
            cur = prev;
        } else {
            prev = cur;
        }
        cur = cur.next;
    }
    return head;
}
```

    The given linked list is sorted in non-decreasing order using absolute values of its nodes. We need to sort the linked list in non-decreasing order using the actual values of the nodes.
1. Start with two pointers, `prev` and `cur` initially pointing to the head and head's next respectively.
2. Traverse the linked list using a while loop.
3. Inside the loop, check if the value of `cur` is less than the value of `prev`.
   - If true, then move the current node to the front of the list, update `prev` and `cur`.
   - Else, set the `prev` to the current node.
4. Continue the traversal until the end of the list is reached.

Time complexity: O(n)

